         Generally they are fine, but when all of a sudden mobs that were balanced according to the previous code (see: velketor the sorceror) start becoming uber powerful, thats not fun.  I'm not sure the extent of the changes on boss mobs which are casters, but if they experienced the same kind of super upgrade, their RvR just plummetted to cloth-caps-in-sleepers level. =<BR>I mean, if all of a sudden Velk got harder than Vindi, this lil change just messed up Velious progression, and basically stopped a lot of guilds from moving on past HoT until they have a zerg army amassed, whereas before you'd go to Velk to practice your techniques and all.  Yeah, great change, really!</P><P>I can't wait to see how guild's who used to do planes now do.  Same shitty drops, more power.  Sometimes you gotta know when not to cross the line between fun and frustrating, and VI did.</P><P>Maybe if they want mobs to be more like their PC counterparts, they won't be quadding for 800 AND casting sunstrike.</P><P>Daedrea Darksoul<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
