        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         <BR>It's broken, and hopefully even VI will see that. Caster mobs have always been extremely dangerous in relation to their con. And a great many spells are too deadly versus PC's, which is why there is the damage reduction on PVP. In addition caster mobs have huge numbers of casting advantages, insane channeling, casting through walls, chain casting spells with long delays. This enormous boost to their power might seem logical but it breaks the game.</P><P>In the meantime expect every melee, who stands next to the mob and can't BoD the damage back, to avoid any and all caster mobs to the greatest of their ability. And forget going into dungeons. The risk reward always used to be doubtful, now the prospect of getting a pull of 2 or 3 uber-nuking mobs means it isn't even worth considering. </P><P><BR> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
